features: ALL PURPOSE CLEANER: Pine-Sol All Purpose Cleaner in a Lavender Clean scent cleans and deodorizes floors, industrial kitchens, restroom facilities and more; Packaging may vary
SAFE ON SURFACES: Pine-Sol concentrate cleaner removes tough messes on indoor and outdoor surfaces including appliances, outdoor furniture, garbage cans, showers, toilets, counters and sinks
CONCENTRATED CLEANER: Concentrated formula can be diluted to deliver 72 gallons of effective cleaning product for heavy cleaning and light touch ups with the long lasting fresh scent of lavender
MULTI-SURFACE CLEANER: Pine Sol powers through tough dirt, grease and grime on a wide variety of surfaces, leaving only a sparkle and the fresh scent of clean behind
GREAT FOR COMMERCIAL USE: From CloroxPro, Pine-Sol is ideal for offices, day care centers, schools, hotels, restaurants and other commercial facilities
body.description: With Pine-Sol Multi-Surface CloroxPro Cleaner, you only need one cleaner to fight dirt, grime and grease, while EPA registered to disinfect and kill 99% of germs on most surfaces throughout your office. Pine-Sol gives you 4X cleaning action and a great, long lasting scent. It deodorizes and wipes out odor causing bacteria leaving a pleasant Pine scent. This concentrated formula cleaner can tackle any challenge, just mix Pine-Sol Multi-Surface Cleaner with water at different strengths to adjust your cleaning power each time, unlike premixed cleaners. Pine-Sol Multi-Surface Cleaner is safe to use on most hard non-porous surfaces including finished hardwood, ceramic tile, linoleum, plastic, and leaves no sticky residue. Pine-Sol Original Pine can also be use to freshen laundry. Ideal for use in schools, daycare centers, restaurants, hotels and other commercial facilities. CloroxPro, Where clean means everything. Packaging May Vary.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars It really does smell like pinesol.
reviews.reviewText: It does smell like the original pinesol just not as strong a pine smell as the real original, but still a good piney clean smell. I had purchased some Pinesol about a year ago from a big box local chain store and had to return it because it smelled so bad. It had a uriney smell!While surfing on Google, I came across an article or site, don't recall exactly where on the net, and discovered other people complaining about it too and then somewhere read that the real original Pinesol had been discontinued or modified and now "Original"Pinesol could only be sold over the internet but using a fraction of the pine oil it used before. So I started searching for pinesol on the internet (Amazon) and looked to make sure the bottle had it printed that it contains pine oil. This bottle does state it has pine oil and it does. Great Price too. Thank you Amazon.
